== About me
I am a PhD candidate at Department of Mathematics, The University of Hong Kong. I am fortunate enough to have [https://www.math.hkbu.edu.hk/~mng/ Prof. Michael K. Ng] as my advisor. I am also fortunate to work with [https://www.comp.nus.edu.sg/~scarlett/ Prof. Jonathan Scarlett] and [https://www.columbia.edu/~my2550/ Prof. Ming Yuan] since my visits. I got my BSc from School of Mathematics, Sun Yat-sen University. 


I'm expected to graduate in June 2025 and seek *postdoc* position that starts in 2025 fall.

== Research 
My research interests include 
- High-dimensional statistics
- Nonconvex optimization
- Signal processing (/e.g./, compressed sensing, phase retrieval, group testing)
- Nonlinear observation (/e.g./, quantization, magnitudes, phases, uniformity)
- Tensor learning (to be explored)


